{0 Resettable Delay Example}

{!module-SpecV2.ResettableDelayExample} is the concrete client of the abstract
theory. It defines:

- the reactive program [resettable_delay_program];
- the assumption and guarantee automata;
- the user invariant used by the generated triples;
- the theorem [resettable_delay_correct].

The final result is obtained through the abstract soundness theorem rather than
by a direct ad hoc proof on traces.
